            <tr>
              <td colspan="5">
                <p class="ia-table-text"><b>What is the problem under consideration? Why is government intervention necessary?</b></p>
                <p class="ia-table-text">Driving under the influence of drugs contributes to or causes road deaths and injury and so is a problem in road safety terms. Although research suggests that the incidence of illegal drug driving is about half that of driving whilst under the influence of alcohol, very few proceedings (i.e. prosecutions) are brought against impaired drivers (less than 2,500 in 2012, compared to 49,000 proceedings brought under the prescribed limit drink driving offence). Primary legislation has been enacted to create a new drug driving offence and Government is required to specify in secondary legislation the controlled drugs to be covered by the new offence and the limit for each. The new offence enables more effective enforcement action to be taken against drug drivers.    </p>
