                <p class="ia-table-text"><b>Description and scale of key monetised costs by ‘main affected groups’ </b></p>
                <p class="ia-table-text">The best estimates of the total monetised costs over the 20 year appraisal period for the Crown Prosecution Service (CPS), criminal justice system, police and offenders are around £22m, £133.5m, £136m and £16m respectively (Present Value). The criminal justice system costs include the costs of the courts, legal aid, prisons and probation. The police costs include the costs of screening suspects and preparation for prosecution. There is an additional cost of £5.7m to business. </p>
